Package org.palladiosimulator.analyzer.slingshot.annotations

Annotation Type ExtensionAnnotation

  • @Documented
@Retention(SOURCE)
@Target(ANNOTATION_TYPE)
public @interface ExtensionAnnotation
    This annotation is used for marking another annotation as a "extension annotation" and can define a shortcut for defining an extension. Instead of using Extension-Annotation, one can use the defined ExtensionAnnotation.
    Author:
    Julijan Katic

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element Description
      Extension extensionPoint
      Defines the extension and maps it to the extension point.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element Description
      java.lang.Class<?> mustBaseOn
      The class that needs to be implemented/extended from.

    • Element Detail

      • extensionPoint

        Extension extensionPoint
        Defines the extension and maps it to the extension point. Typically, the Extension.implementation() is left to its default value, which indicates that the corresponding implementation is the class onto which the defined annotation is annotated.

      • mustBaseOn

        java.lang.Class<?> mustBaseOn
        The class that needs to be implemented/extended from. It is used solely for compile-time validation purposes (and IDE support) and can be left out.
        Default:
        java.lang.Object.class
